urls.title: Introducing the 'BenchmarksWM' R data package
urls.description: In order to create a basis for consensus on which of the many empirical findings working memory (WM) research has produced, Oberauer et al. (2018) have collaborated on identifying and classifying benchmark findings that every theory of WM should strive to explain. We introduce the ‚ÄòBenchmarksWM‚Äô R data package that includes datasets demonstrating the benchmarks with the aim to offer WM theorists, and computational modelers in particular, an easy way to test models by fitting theory-relevant data. The package provides (a) data in a unified format that facilitates processing, (b) detailed documentation of each dataset, and (c) a hierarchical structure of R documentation files in order to conveniently navigate through the content of the package.

tweets.text: Happy to announce the release of the R package 'BenchmarksWM', designed to facilitate theory development in working memory research. Check out the introductory preprint https://t.co/jTkEB9jUjX and give it a try!
